<P>
SATURDAY'S HEROES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Following are last week's top collegiate football performances by South Bay 
high school graduates: 
</P>
<P>
 Ken Sale, Texas-El Paso, senior: The former Bishop Montgomery linebacker had 
three interceptions, returning one 27 yards for a touchdown, and 14 tackles in 
a 34-31 loss to San Diego State. It was the second-best, single-game 
interception mark in UTEP history. 
</P>
<P>
Faasamala Tagaloa, UC Berkeley, senior: The former Bishop Montgomery wide 
receiver had touchdown catches of six and 30 yards in a 25-14 loss to Oregon 
State. Tagaloa leads the Bears with four TDs this season. 
</P>
<P>
George Malauulu, Arizona, freshman: The former Carson quarterback, making his 
first start for the Wildcats, completed five of seven passes for 110 yards and 
one touchdown, and ran 38 yards for another score in a 38-14 win over Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
Errol Sapp, Arizona, freshman: The former Carson running back rushed for 71 
yards on 11 carries in the Wildcats' victory. 
</P>
<P>
Leroy Holt, USC, senior: The former Banning fullback gained 45 yards on 14 
carries and scored the Trojans' second touchdown on a five-yard run in a 19-0 
win over Stanford. 
</P>
<P>
Marvcus Patton, UCLA, senior: The former Leuzinger linebacker had nine tackles, 
two sacks, two caused fumbles and two hurried passes in a 28-27 loss to 
Washington. 
</P>
<P>
Corey Brown, Washington, sophomore: The former Morningside linebacker earned 
the Huskies' "Big Hit" award for the week with his play on special teams 
against UCLA. 
</P>
