<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLU TO MEET MASTER'S IN SOCCER PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal Lutheran, surprisingly seeded third in the National Assn. of 
Intercollegiate Athletics District 3 soccer playoffs, will meet The Master's, 
the second-seeded team, Tuesday in the playoff opener for both schools. The 
game at Master's is scheduled for 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
CLU Coach George Kuntz had speculated that his team might not qualify for the 
playoffs if it lost its season finale to Fresno Pacific, which it did, 1-0. But 
one-goal losses to Westmont and Master's apparently worked to CLU's advantage 
in the Longo System, the formula by which playoff berths are determined. 
</P>
<P>
The Longo system takes into account goals allowed, strength of schedule and 
several other factors. 
</P>
<P>
Master's, 13-4-3 and ranked 13th in the nation, beat Cal Lutheran, 4-3, earlier 
at CLU. The Kingsmen are 11-6-1. 
</P>
