<HEADLINE>
<P>
CARE AND KEEPING OF BANANAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When you bring home a bunch of bananas, you'll want to store them properly so 
they will stay fresh for a long time. 
</P>
<P>
Green-tip bananas will reach their peak of ripeness if you take them out of the 
plastic produce bag and keep them at room temperature. This enables them to 
continue the ripening process and in just a few days they will be tender enough 
for eating. 
</P>
<P>
To store bananas for a longer time, keep them in the refrigerator. The peel 
will darken but the fruit inside will stay ripe and fresh. 
</P>
<P>
Bananas will keep for the longest possible time in the freezer. Just mash the 
fruit with a little lemon juice and freeze it in an airtight container. 
Defrosted, it is perfect to use in a favorite baked goods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
