<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COUNCIL CLEARS WAY FOR BUYING AMTRAK STATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Glendale City Council on Tuesday authorized the city staff to start 
negotiations for the purchase of the Glendale Amtrak station from the Southern 
Pacific Co. as part of a future light-rail route. 
</P>
<P>
City Manager David Ramsay said the council, meeting in closed session, 
identified the 2.5-acre property at 400 W. Cerritos Ave. as a key location in 
the city's transportation plans. Ramsay said the city is also interested in 
preserving the Spanish-style building as a historical site. 
</P>
<P>
The station is on Southern Pacific's main rail line to the San Fernando Valley 
and can be used for an alternative light-rail route to downtown Los Angeles, he 
said. 
</P>
