<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: VALENCIA MAN ARRESTED IN PORNOGRAPHY CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Valencia man was arrested Wednesday on charges stemming from the seizure last 
month of more than 30 child-pornography videotapes and a computer for 
cataloguing his porn collection, the Los Angeles city attorney's office said. 
</P>
<P>
Randall L. Holding, 42, was taken into custody at his Glendale office and was 
being held at the Los Angeles Police Department's Parker Center Jail, said Mike 
Qualls, a spokesman for the city attorney's office. 
</P>
<P>
Holding was charged Tuesday with one count of exhibiting pornography involving 
a minor to a person over 18 years old and one count of exchanging a photograph 
in which a person under the age of 14 is depicted engaging in sexual conduct. 
Holding could be jailed for up to one year and fined as much as $2,000 on each 
count, Qualls said. 
</P>
<P>
Holding, a consultant who finds inexpensive moving companies for clients, was 
arrested once before on Oct. 6 after he showed child-pornography magazines to 
an undercover detective, to whom he also made statements about fondling his 
6-year-old stepdaughter, said Deputy City Atty. Tracy Webb. 
</P>
<P>
The day after his initial arrest, Holding was freed from jail when his wife 
posted $5,000 bail, Qualls said. He is awaiting arraignment on a charge of 
annoying a child in that case, Qualls said. 
</P>
<P>
While searching Holding's house Oct. 6, investigators also seized several 
videocassette recorders, televisions and a video camera, Qualls said. That 
search led to Holding's arrest Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The investigation started in September after detectives received a tip about 
Holding's interest in child pornography, Qualls said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
