<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEALTH CENTERS TO OFFER FREE INFLUENZA VACCINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Free flu immunizations will be available at local county-operated health 
centers and other community sites. It is recommended that immunizations be 
received annually by people over 55 years old and by anyone with a chronic 
heart, lung or kidney disease or certain other chronic conditions. 
</P>
<P>
People with serious egg allergies or those who have a serious illness should 
consult a physician before receiving the flu vaccine. 
</P>
<P>
Some of the free influenza clinics are scheduled as follows. For information 
about clinics where no telephone number is listed, call Harbor Health Center, 
519-6109; Torrance Health Center, 533-6562; Wilmington Health Center, 549-4550. 
</P>
<P>
Today, 9 a.m.-2 p.m.; Conference Room, first floor, San Pedro Peninsula 
Hospital, 1300 W. 7th St., San Pedro. 
</P>
<P>
Friday, 9-11 a.m.; Wilmington Health Center, 1325 Broad Ave., Wilmington. 
</P>
<P>
Saturday, 9 a.m.-1 p.m.; FHP Inc., 29050 Western Ave., Suite 101, San Pedro. 
</P>
<P>
Tuesday, 1-3 p.m.; Torrance Health Center, 2300 Carson St., Torrance. 
</P>
<P>
Tuesday, noon-2 p.m.; El Segundo Medical Center, 455 Main St., El Segundo; 
322-1611. Wednesday, 10 a.m.-noon; Wilmington Senior Center, 1148 N. Avalon 
Blvd., Wilmington. 
</P>
<P>
Nov. 11, 10 a.m.-2 p.m.; Centinela Hospital Airport Medical Clinic, 9601 S. 
Sepulveda Blvd., Los Angeles; 215-6020. 
</P>
<P>
Nov. 14, 1-3 p.m.; Harbor Health Center, 122 W. 8th St., San Pedro. 
</P>
<P>
Nov. 16, 10 a.m.-noon; Clark Stadium, 861 Valley Drive, Hermosa Beach. 
</P>
