<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: PICO RIVERA; 
</P>
<P>
TEACHERS PICKET EL RANCHO DISTRICT FOR 10% PAY RAISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 150 teachers and counselors picketed outside the El Rancho Unified 
School District offices in Pico Rivera after classes earlier this week to 
pressure officials for a pay increase and better health benefits. Teachers are 
asking for 10% pay increases this year and next. 
</P>
<P>
The district is offering a 4.64% boost for one year and is seeking to impose a 
teacher discipline policy. District negotiator John Sherman said, "Teachers 
have different things that they are requesting and the district is analyzing 
the budget to see how far they can go to meet the teachers' request." 
</P>
<P>
Another negotiating session is scheduled for Friday. 
</P>
