<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: BEL-AIR; 
</P>
<P>
EXPLORING JEWISH HUMOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jewish humor will be the subject of a daylong seminar Sunday at the University 
of Judaism. 
</P>
<P>
Co-sponsored by the university and UCLA Extension, the program will feature 
Moshe Waldoks, author of "The Big Book of Jewish Humor," and Allan Gould, 
co-author of "The Unorthodox Book of Jewish Records and Lists." 
</P>
<P>
Part lecture, part discussion and part cabaret-style performance, the program 
will include consideration of such topics as "Messianists, Medicine Men and 
Movable Furniture: A Short History of Jewish Humor" and "Laughing and Keeping 
from Crying: The Jewish Joke and Jewish Humor." 
</P>
<P>
The program will be held at the University of Judaism, 15600 Mulholland Drive, 
Bel-Air, from 9:30 a.m. to 5 p.m. Tickets are $60, $48.75 for seniors. For more 
information, call UCLA Extension at 825-2301. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA110289-0099 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 128933 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 2, 1989, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
