<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHO'S HOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ivan Wilson of South Gate High rushed for 172 yards and threw a 40-yard 
touchdown pass as the Rams beat Locke, 27-22, for their 21st straight victory. 
</P>
<P>
Gahr High's Randy Donisthorpe completed 10 of 15 passes for 198 yards and three 
TDs in a 44-3 rout of Warren. 
</P>
<P>
Mayfair won its first Suburban League game in two years, 21-15, over previously 
unbeaten Glenn. 
</P>
<P>
St. Paul's Matt Borunda passed for three touchdowns and ran for another as the 
Swordsmen crushed Servite, 38-6. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Kortenhoeven of Valley Christian rushed for 115 yards and two TDs as the 
Crusaders beat Miraleste, 28-14, to stay undefeated. 
</P>
