<P>
November 2, 1989, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 13; Column 6; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
74 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGELS ASK WAIVERS ON GLENN HOFFMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Angels asked waivers on infielder Glenn Hoffman Wednesday for the purpose 
of giving him his release. 
</P>
<P>
Hoffman, 31, joined the Angels as a free agent last January. During the 1989 
season, he appeared in 48 games and had 22 hits in 104 at-bats for a .212 
average. He had one home run and drove in three runs. 
</P>
<P>
Hoffman appeared at all four infield positions and made his first career starts 
as a first baseman and as a designated hitter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
