<P>
Homes More Affordable Statewide: Statewide housing affordability improved in 
September for the second month in a row as buyers increasingly sought homes in 
more affordable communities, the California Assn. of Realtors said. Eighteen 
percent of households earned the income needed to qualify for a mortgage loan 
to purchase the median-priced, existing single-family home, up from 17% in 
August but still down from 22% a year ago. In the Los Angeles region, 14% could 
qualify to purchase the median-priced home, up from 12%. At the September 
median price of $221,954 in Los Angeles, a household here needed an annual 
income of $73,118 and faced monthly mortgage payments of $1,828. 
