<HEADLINE>
<P>
ELDERLY WOMAN KILLED WHEN CAR HITS TRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An elderly woman was killed Wednesday when her car crashed into a trash truck 
at a busy Fullerton intersection. 
</P>
<P>
Louise Maxine Bartoletti, of Fullerton, was driving her Cadillac east on 
Malvern Avenue. She struck the truck, which was making a left turn on to 
Malvern from West Gilbert Street, Fullerton Police Sgt. Steve Matson said. 
</P>
<P>
Parademics took the woman to St. Jude Hospital and Rehabilitation Center in 
Fullerton, where she was pronounced dead. The truck driver was unhurt. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton police have not determined which driver failed to yield the right of 
way, Matson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
