<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN IS KILLED TRYING TO AID COUNTY DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Russell McCampbell, a 31-year-old San Diego man, was running to help a stricken 
Orange County driver Wednesday when he was hit and killed by a car. 
</P>
<P>
The California Highway Patrol reported that John Antenucci of Laguna Niguel was 
driving north on I-805 at 3:40 a.m. when he took the Balboa Avenue off-ramp, 
ran through a sign, jumped the curb, plowed over a flower patch and ended up 
back on the freeway exit. His car rolled and ended upright. 
</P>
<P>
The CHP said McCampbell ran across the freeway to aid Antenucci, but another 
vehicle then struck Antenucci's car, which in turn hit McCampbell. He was 
pronounced dead at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
Antenucci was hospitalized in the intensive care unit of Sharp Memorial 
Hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
