<HEADLINE>
<P>
BALLET; 
</P>
<P>
NUREYEV TALKS MAY END HOLDOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rudolf Nureyev will meet the head of the Paris Opera Ballet later this month, 
raising hopes that the dancer-director's contract dispute with the company 
might eventually be settled, an opera spokesman said today. 
</P>
<P>
The 51-year-old Soviet defector, who is insisting on new terms, agreed to meet 
French Opera Chairman Pierre Berge at the end of November. 
</P>
<P>
Nureyev has directed the ballet since 1983. But his relations with the Paris 
Opera Ballet reached an all-time low last month when the company began its new 
season with temporary replacements for its temperamental star, who had refused 
to return from the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
